<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1222] add convenience methods for deleteById to take a list of strings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1222</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a patch to add methods to SolrServer.java and UpdateRequest.java to accept a list of Strings for deleteById. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Internally, UpdateRequest uses a list for the single api, but SolrServer calls process immediately after the single so it would send all my deletes to the server one by one. This change adds a method to UpdateRequest to add a List to the internal list, SolrServer calls this method then process immediately after.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would be nice if you can get this in for 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
